<DocsLayout
  title="Troubleshooting"
  description="BudgetBaby troubleshooting: quick fixes, symptom lookup table, how to generate a support report, and per-issue solutions."
  canonical="/budgetbaby/docs/troubleshooting"
  headings={headings}
>
  <div class="docs-content">
    <h1>Troubleshooting</h1>
    <p class="docs-summary">
      Most BudgetBaby issues are resolved in a few steps. Start with the quick fixes below,
      then use the symptom table to find your specific issue. If nothing here helps,
      generate a support report and send it to the support team.
    </p>

    <h2 id="quick-fixes">Quick fixes to try first</h2>
    <p>Before diving into specific issues, run through these four checks. They resolve the majority of reported problems.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Force-quit and reopen the app.</strong> Swipe up from the Home bar to enter the app switcher, swipe BudgetBaby off the screen, then reopen it.</li>
      <li><strong>Check your iOS version.</strong> BudgetBaby requires iOS 17.0 or later. Go to Settings → General → About to check. Update if you are on an older version.</li>
      <li><strong>Update the app.</strong> Open the App Store, tap your profile icon, and pull down to check for updates. Many issues are fixed in recent releases.</li>
      <li><strong>Check your internet connection.</strong> Cloud backup, sync, and Premium restore all require a working internet connection.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="symptom-table">Symptom lookup table</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Symptom</th>
