            <th>Fix</th>
            <th>Contact support when</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Safe to Spend shows 0 or a negative number</td>
            <td>Unpaid Critical bills exceed remaining budget, or income is entered incorrectly</td>
            <td>Mark paid bills as paid; check income in Settings → Budget Setup; tap the info button to see the full breakdown</td>
            <td>Numbers still do not match after following the Safe to Spend steps below</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Transactions appear on the wrong day</td>
            <td>Timezone handling issue fixed in v2.0.5</td>
            <td>Update the app; re-save affected transactions to apply the fix to existing records</td>
            <td>Dates are still wrong after updating to the latest version</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Premium not active after purchase</td>
            <td>App Store cache or wrong Apple ID signed in</td>
            <td>Settings → Premium → Restore Purchases; wait 30 seconds; force-quit and reopen</td>
            <td>Restore fails after confirming you are signed in with the purchasing Apple ID</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Cloud backup fails</td>
            <td>Not signed in, no internet, or backup slot full</td>
            <td>Sign in at Settings → Account; check connection; delete existing backup if slot is full</td>
            <td>All steps tried and backup still fails</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Notifications not arriving</td>
            <td>iOS notification permission denied, or wrong days selected</td>
            <td>iOS Settings → BudgetBaby → Notifications → Allow Notifications; check Settings → Reminders</td>
            <td>Permission is enabled, reminders are configured correctly, and notifications still do not arrive</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
