    <h2 id="diagnostics">Generating a support report</h2>
    <p>
      BudgetBaby has a built-in diagnostics engine that packages everything the support team needs
      to understand what is happening on your device, without ever including your financial data.
      For anything beyond a simple question, attaching a support report speeds up resolution significantly.
    </p>
    <h3>How to generate a report</h3>
    <p>Go to <strong>Settings → Support and Diagnostics</strong>. You have three options:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Report a Problem</strong> (recommended for bugs). Tap "Start Report." The guided 5-step flow asks which area is affected and when the issue occurred. It then generates a full diagnostics bundle and prompts you to send it. Choose your area: Backup, Restore, Bills, Subscriptions, Spending Buckets, Money on Hand, Premium, or Other.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Export Diagnostics</strong> (quick, no prompts). One tap creates the bundle immediately. Use this if you want to capture the current app state without going through the guided flow.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Copy Support Report</strong> (for pasting into emails). Copies a plain-text summary to your clipboard. Useful if you are writing from a desktop or want to paste the report inline.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>What is in the report</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Events log.</strong> Last 24 hours of app activity, up to 2,000 events. No financial data: only action types, screen names, and outcomes.</li>
      <li><strong>Device snapshot.</strong> iPhone model, iOS version, locale, timezone, and build type (App Store or TestFlight).</li>
      <li><strong>App state.</strong> Version, build number, onboarding status, Premium status, backup count, and last backup/restore dates.</li>
      <li><strong>Data fingerprint.</strong> Entity counts only: how many transactions, categories, bills, periods, and goals. No amounts or descriptions.</li>
      <li><strong>Support story.</strong> A human-readable narrative that summarizes the event timeline and highlights anything unusual.</li>
      <li><strong>Issue fingerprint.</strong> A unique <code>BB-XXXX-XXXX</code> identifier for your report. Include this in your email subject line.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="doc-tip">
      <strong>Your financial data is never included.</strong> No transaction amounts, descriptions, account names, balances, budget values, or category names appear in the report. Only anonymous counts and app-state metadata.
    </div>
    <h3>How to send it</h3>
    <p>
      After generating the report, iOS presents a share sheet. The fastest route is Mail.
      BudgetBaby pre-fills the subject line with your support code (<code>BB-XXXX-XXXX</code>)
      and attaches the bundle automatically. Send to
      <a href="mailto:support@babyblocks.io">support@babyblocks.io</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      If Mail is not configured, use AirDrop to your Mac and attach the file manually,
      or use Copy Support Report to paste the text summary into your email.
    </p>
    <h3>Report archive</h3>
    <p>
      Every report is saved under Settings → Support and Diagnostics → View Archive.
      Reports are kept for 90 days. You can re-share any archived report without regenerating it.
    </p>
    <p>The bundle filename looks like:</p>
    <div class="doc-formula">BudgetBaby_Diagnostics_2026-03-01_14-35_BB-9F3K-2A17.budgetbaby-diagnostics</div>

    <h2 id="safe-to-spend-wrong">Safe to Spend looks wrong</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Tap the info button next to Safe to Spend on the home screen to see the full calculation breakdown with your actual numbers.</li>
      <li>Verify your active budget period dates are correct in Settings → Budget Setup.</li>
      <li>Check that upcoming bills are assigned to the current period and that any paid bills are marked as paid. Unpaid Critical bills are reserved in the calculation.</li>
      <li>Confirm that your savings allocation percentage in Budget Setup matches your intentions.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      If Safe to Spend is 0 or negative and you do not expect it to be, the most common causes are:
      unpaid Critical bills that exceed the remaining budget, or an income amount that was entered
      incorrectly during setup.
    </p>

    <h2 id="premium-not-unlocking">Premium not unlocking after purchase</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Go to Settings → Premium → Restore Purchases.</li>
      <li>Wait 30 seconds after tapping Restore, then check again.</li>
      <li>Force-quit and reopen the app.</li>
      <li>Make sure you are signed in to the App Store with the Apple ID that made the purchase. Go to Settings → (your name) → Media and Purchases to verify.</li>
      <li>Contact <a href="/budgetbaby/support">support</a> with your order number if the issue persists.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="date-issues">Transaction date issues</h2>
    <p>
      BudgetBaby normalizes all transaction dates to noon UTC to prevent timezone-related date shifts
      across time zones. If you see dates that are off by one day:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Update BudgetBaby to the latest version. v2.0.5 and later include this fix.</li>
      <li>Re-save any affected transactions. Opening a transaction and tapping Save applies the timezone normalization to that record.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="backup-fails">Backup fails</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Verify you are signed in to your BudgetBaby account at Settings → Account.</li>
      <li>Check your internet connection. Backups require an active connection during upload.</li>
      <li>Free users have 1 backup slot. If it is occupied, delete the existing backup first at Settings → Account → Manage Backups.</li>
      <li>If errors persist after trying all of the above, contact <a href="/budgetbaby/support">support</a> with your account email address.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="notifications">Notifications not arriving</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Open iOS Settings → BudgetBaby → Notifications. Ensure Allow Notifications is turned on.</li>
      <li>In BudgetBaby, go to Settings → Reminders. Verify the reminder days and time are configured as you expect.</li>
      <li>Check that quiet hours are not covering the time when you expect the notification.</li>
      <li>Note: Same-day bill reminders are available on the free tier. Multi-day reminders (3 days before, 1 week before) and subscription reminders require Premium.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="app-crashes">App crashes on launch</h2>
    <p>Crashes on launch are rare and usually caused by an outdated app version or a corrupted local data store.</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Update BudgetBaby to the latest version from the App Store.</li>
      <li>If the crash continues after updating and you have a cloud backup, restore from it: sign in on another device or reinstall the app, then restore from Settings → Backup and Restore.</li>
      <li>If you do not have a cloud backup, contact <a href="mailto:support@babyblocks.io">support@babyblocks.io</a> before uninstalling. Include your iOS version and app version. We may be able to help recover your data.</li>
      <li>As a last resort, uninstall and reinstall the app. This will delete all local data.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
